<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-486-674  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 486 674.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  May 21 1990 v12 n21 p80(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Microstep enables graphics programming: program boasts aprogramming language and utilities, but at a high price. (SoftwareReview) (Syscorp International's Microstep 1.4) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pavlac, Ross.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Syscorp International's Microstep 1.4 is a graphics programminglanguage with computer-aided software engineering (CASE)capabilities.andP;  The program contains three main components: agraphics-based specification language, an application generator,and a set of run-time utilities.andP;  The mouse-based icons andwindows are somewhat similar to Microsoft Windows.andP;  A system isdesigned by placing hierarchical flowchart-like icons on thescreen to represent databases, files, operations, and reports.andO;The structure is specified within each icon.andP;  An application isdesigned and compiled by choosing the Install option, but can beaccomplished step-by-step to provide more control over debuggingor to save C code for archiving purposes.andP;  The program is simple,surprisingly easy to use, and contains several handy tools.andP;  The$7,500 price may prove prohibitive.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Syscorp International Inc. (products).andO;Product:   Microstep 1.4 (Program development software).andO;Topic:     EvaluationSoftware PackagesGraphics LanguagesComputer-Aided Software Engineering.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>